The co-founder of Fly Fitness Factory, Mr Bolarinwa Kashif popularly known as Mr Fly has stated that the organisation — Fly Fitness Factory — is aimed at contributing to society. He said, “Our plan is to contribute to society, not just to make money, it is a people over profit type of organisation.” Kashif noted that the vision of the organisation is that “one day, every day, every member of the society and those who will visit where we operate shall understand the need for a healthy lifestyle and strive to live one.” Also, the co-founder of the organisation, Omotara Akanni popularly known as Motara while speaking on the philosophy of the organisation, said “we will constantly lead the society to a healthy lifestyle, hold their hands through the journey in reaching healthy lifestyle goals and in the ambience they will love. As alumni of The Polytechnic of Ibadan, they both decided to give back to the school from which they graduated excellently, by providing jerseys to a department, as well as sponsoring a football activity for the department (HOD cup). Speaking on the numerous exploits of the organisation, Akanni said, “for example, we have a special package for students, corps members and widows, we have also taken it upon ourselves to support them every month by giving them a certain amount of money to take care of their basic needs. “Above all, there is a package for pregnant women, taking into consideration the amount of expenses they incur during pregnancy, we have decided to make this package free for the pregnant mothers,” Akanni said. Kashif explained that the primary mission of the organisation is to continue to provide good fitness services with a clean, comfortable ambience that enhance the experience and satisfaction of and perception of value. 